Fire at Estonian Orphanage Kills 10 Disabled People

-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 
2011-02-21T06:55:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/fire-at-estonian-orphanage-kills-10-disabled-people.html
Fire at an orphanage for the
disabled in Haapsalu, western  Estonia , killed 10 people
yesterday, the rescue service said.  Eight children under 16 and two patients aged 20-21 died
after the wooden building caught fire at around 2:30 p.m., the
rescue service said in an e-mailed statement today. Two people
were taken to hospital.  Police are investigating the cause of the fire. The last
fire safety checks at the orphanage on Jan. 19 showed no
violations, the service said.  The government declared Feb. 21 a day of mourning.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
 oummelas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
